comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T11:15:27.740Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: focused Windows-tolerant filesystem assertion lane remains linked. Focused test command is linked on the item; local Linux suite accepts EACCES|EPERM and EISDIR|EPERM while preserving POSIX coverage. GH-427 should be confirmed by the next Windows Node 24 nightly after push."
  "2026-07-04T11:42:53.435Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update: Windows-tolerant filesystem assertion lane remains covered in the combined branch. Local verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/restore-command.spec.ts tests/unit/core/history/history-rewrite.spec.ts; full coverage 263 files / 5337 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, lines; pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint. GH-427 still needs confirmation from GitHub Windows Node 24 CI/nightly after push."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T08:13:21.922Z",maintainer-agent,"Fix applied (uncommitted): restore-command.spec 3x rejects.toMatchObject code now expect.stringMatching(/^(EACCES|EPERM)$/); history-rewrite.spec EISDIR assertion now toMatch(/EISDIR|EPERM/). Both spec files pass locally (42 tests). Root cause: Windows Node 24 fs raises EPERM where POSIX raises EACCES (read-only append) / EISDIR (write to dir path)."
  "2026-07-04T10:38:37.025Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 verification: platform-tolerant assertions pass in the full fast suite (5336/5336) on Linux; the EACCES|EPERM / EISDIR|EPERM alternations keep POSIX coverage while accepting Windows Node 24 EPERM. Windows confirmation will come from the next nightly after push (GH-427 stays open until then)."
